title: Const generics out of range when substituting substs=[]

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
This issue does *NOT* occur on nightly, so perhaps it's a duplicate that has already been fixed, but I could not find a similar issue on github. Feel free to close if this has already been fixed :) ### Code ```Rust #[repr(u8)] enum T::A as u8 + T::<0>::B as u8 }> { A = 1, B } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.63.0 ``` ### Error output ``` error: internal compiler error: compiler/rustc_middle/src/ty/subst.rs:639:17: const parameter `N/#0` (Const { ty: u8, kind: Param(N/#0) }/0) out of range when substituting substs=[] ```
